# Use Glean MCP for Google Docs

When a user shares a Google Docs link, always use the Glean MCP `read_document` tool to fetch the content instead of `WebFetch`. WebFetch will hit Google's sign-in wall and fail.

``` 
CallMcpTool(server: "user-glean_default", toolName: "read_document", arguments: { urls: ["<google-doc-url>"] })
```

The `urls` parameter accepts an array of URLs. This works for any document indexed by Glean (Google Docs, Confluence, etc.).
